JOHANNESBURG - Poet and spoken-word performer, Myesha Jenkins, is known for her feminist outlook and a writing style that is open, descriptive, revealing and sometimes challenging. Her book To Breathe Into Another Voice: A South African Anthology of Jazz Poetry brings together the work of 45 South African poets reflecting on the experience of jazz in their lives.  In five sections, the book reveals some of the impacts this genre of music has had:  The Power of Music, This Thing Called Jazz, They Make the Music, Some of Them Were Special and All About Living. The anthology is the first of its kind in SA and features work from new writers as well as experienced poets, speaks equally in female and male voices, representing all of South Africa’s racial groups. Jenkins spoke to Weekend Wake Up's Ayanda-Allie Payne. Watch the video of the interview above. eNCA